message:
Hi Stephen, I think the API for DeferralManager  has slightly changed. In AsyncEx 5.0, this is how I did it:

    public class MyEventArgs : EventArgs
    {
      private readonly DeferralManager deferrals = new DeferralManager();

      ... // Your own constructors and properties.

      public IDisposable GetDeferral()
      {
        return deferrals.DeferralSource.GetDeferral();
      }

      internal Task WaitForDeferralsAsync()
      {
        return deferrals.WaitForDeferralsAsync();
      }
    }

Hope it looks good :)
